Noise levels are being tested on rollercoaster at Flambards in Helston over the Easter period . 
  Reading on 'fright' decibels of the ride will be recorded as planning council considers 480-home development nearby . 
  Theme park owner Ian Cunningham said he was 'amazed' the homes will be built right next door . 
  Developer David Martin has applied for the housing estate next door to the theme park . 
 